## Process

<!-- Copy this Process section exactly as written, without modification: -->

Work through the commits in order. For each one:

1. Write a test that reproduces the bug and watch it fail (red), implement the simplest fix to make it pass (green), then refactor while keeping tests green. Pure refactor commits add no behavior, so just keep the existing tests green.
2. Present the unstaged diff for review, then commit on approval using the `ls-git:git-commit` skill.
3. If implementation becomes blocked, STOP and seek guidance from the user.
4. STOP and wait for user feedback before moving to the next commit.

Once the bug is fixed, document:

- What the root cause was
- Why the bug occurred
- How the fix addresses the underlying issue
- Any preventive measures to avoid similar bugs in the future
